      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of offset distances and load rates; environmental controls (temperature, humidity) documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 offset (44 mm) and a single crosshead displacement rate (25 mm/min) at ambient temperature. Although this single condition is the standard protocol, it does not span the range of in-vivo loading variability. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3; this gap is documented and accepted given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard test and no alternative multi-condition protocol exists."
    },
